    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Dungeoneer's Handbook pg. 28</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> faint evocation <strong>CL</strong> 5th</p><p><strong>Slot</strong> weapon quality; <strong>Price</strong> +1 bonus; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>Upon command, a <em>breaking </em>weapon deals an extra 2d6 points of damage against inanimate objects and crystalline creatures on a successful hit and ignores the hardness of objects with a hardness of 5 or lower. When used against a crystalline creature, the damage from this effect does not stack with bane or similar weapon special abilities. This effect remains until another command is given.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>break</em> or <em>shatter</em>; <strong>Price</strong> -</p>",
